{"lemma":"سِلْسِلَة","slug":"سِلْسِلَة","root":"س.ل.س.ل","root_slug":"س-ل-س-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-س-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سِلْسِلَة","root":"سلسل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20285","n20302","n20303"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"iron chain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chain","tags":["figuratively","literally"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of rope or cord","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"series"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic שִׁלְשֶׁלְתָּא (šilšeltā, “chain”), from Akkadian 𒉠𒂡𒂡 (/⁠šeršerratu⁠/, “chains”), likely onomatopoeic of rattling chains; cognates with (Hebrew שַׁרְשֶׁרֶת (sharshéret), Classical Syriac ܫܝܫܠܬܐ (šēšaltā), Amharic ሰንሰለት (sänsälät), Old Armenian շղթայ (šłtʻay), Sumerian 𒋢𒂡𒂡 (/⁠šeršer⁠/, “chains”) likely derived from the common Semitic."},"ipa":["/sil.si.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20285","headword_ar":"سَلْسَلَةٌ","root":"sl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulosila","text_ar":"سُلْسِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musalosalN","text_ar":"مُسَلْسَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below)] signifies A thing's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being connected"},{"kind":"text","text":"with another thing. (M, K.) [It is also inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salosala","text_ar":"سَلْسَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as such signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"connecting"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing with another thing.] ―         -b2-  [Hence, or the reverse may be the case,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salosalotuhu","text_ar":"سَلْسَلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I bound him with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosilap","text_ar":"سِلْسِلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O. TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salosalotu AlmaA='a fiY AlHaloqi","text_ar":"سَلْسَلْتُ المَا=ءَ فِى الحَلْقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I poured the water into the throat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fauces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a continuous stream."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, * O.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAsalosala TaEaAmFA","text_ar":"مَاسَلْسَلَ طَعَامًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did not eat food:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) as though he did not pour it into his throat, or fauces. (TA.)       -A2-  Accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salosala","text_ar":"سَلْسَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salosalap","text_ar":"سَلْسَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long piece of a camel's hump."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)       -A3-  See also 1, third sentence."}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n20302","headword_ar":"سَلْسَلَةٌ","root":"sl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.: see R. Q. 1.       -A2-  Also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long piece of a camel's hump:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K:) accord. to AA, it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasolasapN","text_ar":"لَسْلَسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisolisapN","text_ar":"لِسْلِسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20303","headword_ar":"سِلْسِلَةٌ","root":"sl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chain, i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinojiyro","text_ar":"زِنْجِيرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in Pers.; (KL;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rings"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irN","text_ar":"دَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. used as a coll. gen. n., though I do not know any authority for such usage of it,] K [in the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irapN","text_ar":"دَايِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of metals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alosalapu","text_ar":"السَّلْسَلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ the being connected ” with another thing: (M: [see R. Q. 1:]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsilu","text_ar":"سَلَاسِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh, TA.) It was a custom to extend a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosilap","text_ar":"سِلْسِلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"over a river or a road, the ships or beats or the passengers being arrested thereby, for the purpose of the taking of the tithes from them by an officer set over it. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosilapu baroqK","text_ar":"سِلْسِلَةُ بَرْقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An elongated stream of lightning"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a chain"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the midst of the clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA: *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsilu Albaroqi","text_ar":"سَلَاسِلُ البَرْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what have assumed the form of chains"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAtasalosala","text_ar":"مَاتَسَلْسَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of lightning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the clouds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the clouds"},{"kind":"text","text":"in like manner]: (K: [but I think that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~aHaAbi","text_ar":"وَالسَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K is evidently a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"فِى السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the reading in the M:]) sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosilapN","text_ar":"سِلْسِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosilN","text_ar":"سِلْسِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) thus in the copies of the K, but in the L ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosiylN","text_ar":"سِلْسِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is [said to be] the correct"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1398},{"kind":"text","text":"word. (TA. [See, however, what follows.]) And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsilu Alr~amoli","text_ar":"سَلَاسِلُ الرَّمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What have assumed the form of chains"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tasalosala","text_ar":"مَا تَسَلْسَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsilu","text_ar":"سَلَاسِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sands that become accumulated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"congested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanoEaqidu","text_ar":"يَنْعَقِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one upon another, and extended along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, O, K, TA:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramolN *uwsalaAsila","text_ar":"رَمْلٌ ذُوسَلَاسِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sands having portions accumulated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"congested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu salaAsila","text_ar":"ذَاتُ سَلَاسِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has been expl. as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elongated sands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosilapN","text_ar":"سِلْسِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siloslN","text_ar":"سِلْسلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosiylN","text_ar":"سِلْسِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~amoli","text_ar":"الرَّمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salosuwlu","text_ar":"سَلْسُولُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h [to the first letter], is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silosiyluhu","text_ar":"سِلْسِيلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsilu kitaAbK","text_ar":"سَلَاسِلُ كِتَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lines of a book"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biro*awonN *uw salaAsila","text_ar":"بِرْذَوْنٌ ذُو سَلَاسِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hackney"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon whose legs one sees what resemble"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAsil","text_ar":"سَلَاسِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chains"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHarap","text_ar":"وَحَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small reptile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of lizard, the same that is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alsilosilapu Alr~aqoTaA='u","text_ar":"السِلْسِلَةُ الرَّقْطَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroqaTu","text_ar":"اَرْقَطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spotted, black and white, having a slender tail, which it moves about when running."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","O"]}]}}